# Multi-line code must survive

The sketch's regex converter destroyed every element spanning lines. This fixture is the permanent regression test.

```
fn main() {
    let xs: Vec<i32> = (0..10).collect();
    // angle brackets <T> and ampersands && stay intact
    let sum: i32 = xs.iter().sum();
    println!("{sum}");
}
```

Inline spans like `Vec<String>` too, plus a paragraph that itself spans several source lines.

```
SELECT id, title
FROM articles
WHERE content_text MATCH 'wal'
ORDER BY rank;
```
